HEADWORD: Peritricha
<hw>Pe*rit"ri*cha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>peri`</grk> about + <?/, <?/, hair.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of ciliated Infusoria having a circle
of cilia around the oral disk and sometimes another around the body. It
includes the vorticellas. See <er>Vorticella</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peritrochium</ent>⟦br⟧
